14. The roadmap I would give you as a C tutor

Here is the order I would use.

Phase 1 — stabilize current program

Do this first:

normalize names and units,
support singular/plural aliases,
improve file format,
add total nutrient summary,
separate conversion data from code a little better.
Phase 2 — redesign the data model

Introduce:

Food
Serving
Nutrient
FoodNutrient
Entry

Even if still stored in plain files.

Phase 3 — move storage to SQLite

This is where the project becomes serious.

Phase 4 — import real food data

Either:

USDA downloadable data, or
API-based fetching.
Phase 5 — improve usability

Add:

food search,
suggestions,
date-based logs,
daily reports,
update/delete entries,
favorite foods,
custom foods.
Phase 6 — production polish

Add:

error handling,
logging,
tests,
documentation,
config file,
separation into modules.
